---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Web Development" description="Direct AI to build real web software. Six projects from static site to production system.">
  <h1 class="mb-4">AI-First Web Development</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">You direct AI to build real software. Not tutorials, not exercises — deployed products. You define the problem, plan the solution, direct the implementation, review every change, and ship to a live URL.</p>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">The output isn't "I understand React." It's "I shipped six deployed products and I can explain every decision I made."</p>

  <!-- How this compares -->
  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-10">How this compares</h2>
  <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Classic CS degree</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Learn to code first, build later. Deep theory, slow path to shipping.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Bootcamps</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Guided projects, you write every line. Fast path, but the skill is writing code.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">AI-assisted tutorials</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">AI helps you write code. You're still the maker — AI is the assistant.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border-2 border-primary rounded-lg p-5 bg-primary-bg">
      <p class="font-semibold text-sm mb-1">This</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">You direct AI to write it. You learn to plan, review, verify, and deploy. The output is shipped products + the judgment to direct any tech project.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- The development process -->
  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-10">The development process — and what changes</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-6">Every project follows the same 8-step software development lifecycle. AI changes <em>how</em> you do each step, not <em>whether</em> you do it.</p>

  <div class="space-y-8 mb-6">

    <!-- 1. Requirements -->
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Requirements</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">You define the problem. AI refines ambiguous requirements, spots gaps, and generates user stories from a brief — but you own the scope.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Connector -->
    <div class="flex justify-center"><div class="w-[1.5px] h-6 bg-border"></div></div>

    <!-- 2. Design -->
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Design</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">You define UX intent. AI generates wireframe concepts, suggests patterns, and prototypes layouts — but you validate against user needs.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Connector -->
    <div class="flex justify-center"><div class="w-[1.5px] h-6 bg-border"></div></div>

    <!-- 3. Architecture -->
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Architecture</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">AI proposes system design, data models, and tech stack. You need to understand enough to challenge it — and you make the final call.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Connector -->
    <div class="flex justify-center"><div class="w-[1.5px] h-6 bg-border"></div></div>

    <!-- 4. Implementation -->
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Implementation</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">The biggest shift. AI writes the code. You direct, review, and iterate. Your work is in prompts, specs, and code review — not syntax.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Connector -->
    <div class="flex justify-center"><div class="w-[1.5px] h-6 bg-border"></div></div>

    <!-- 5. Testing -->
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">5</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Testing</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">AI generates tests and identifies edge cases. You validate they cover the acceptance criteria from step 1.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Connector -->
    <div class="flex justify-center"><div class="w-[1.5px] h-6 bg-border"></div></div>

    <!-- 6. Deployment -->
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">6</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Deployment</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Largely the same. AI writes pipeline configs, Dockerfiles, and infrastructure-as-code. Once set up, it's automated.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Connector -->
    <div class="flex justify-center"><div class="w-[1.5px] h-6 bg-border"></div></div>

    <!-- 7. UAT -->
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">7</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">UAT</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">No change. Show the client the staging site. Collect feedback, turn it into tickets, iterate. Humans validating with humans.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Connector -->
    <div class="flex justify-center"><div class="w-[1.5px] h-6 bg-border"></div></div>

    <!-- 8. Monitoring -->
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">8</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">Monitoring</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">AI helps interpret logs, analyse usage patterns, and suggest fixes. You own the feedback loop and decide what to iterate on.</p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8"><strong class="text-text">You move from maker to director, but you never lose ownership.</strong> Every step still requires your judgment — AI changes the tools, not the responsibility.</p>

  <!-- The Roles -->
  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-10">The roles</h2>
  <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3 mb-8">
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
      <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-2xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3">D</div>
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2">You — the Director</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Decide what gets built, review the work, verify it's correct, sign off on every change.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
      <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-2xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3">C</div>
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2">Claude Code — AI Developer</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Writes code, creates files, runs tests, opens pull requests. Fast and capable, but makes mistakes.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
      <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-full bg-primary-bg text-primary font-bold text-2xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3">G</div>
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2">Gemini — AI Reviewer</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Independently reviews every pull request for security issues and best practices.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- The Progression -->
  <h2 class="mb-4 mt-10">The progression</h2>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-6">Six projects. Each repeats the same loop with one new capability — and one shift in what's expected of you as a Director.</p>

  <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
    <Card title="Project 1: The Static Site" metadata="Foundation" href="/web-dev/projects/1">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-2">A professional business website for a landscaping company. Deployed to a live URL.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-2">+1: You learn the loop — branch, direct, verify, merge</p>
    </Card>
    <Card title="Project 2: The Dynamic App" metadata="Foundation" href="/web-dev/projects/2">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-2">A full-stack facts app. React, FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Docker, CI, Gemini reviewer.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-2">+1: You learn to verify systems — databases, APIs, containers</p>
    </Card>
    <Card title="Project 3: The Interactive App" metadata="Coming soon">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-2">Forms, validation, email. You plan it yourself from a client brief.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-2">+1: You write the PRD — planning judgment becomes the new skill</p>
    </Card>
    <Card title="Project 4: The Integrated App" metadata="Coming soon">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-2">Third-party API integration (Stripe, Google Maps, or similar).</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-2">+1: You verify against external documentation — hallucination detection</p>
    </Card>
    <Card title="Project 5: The Multi-User App" metadata="Coming soon">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-2">Auth, roles, permissions. Different users see different things.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-2">+1: You think adversarially — can you break your own access controls?</p>
    </Card>
    <Card title="Project 6: The Live System" metadata="Capstone" href="/web-dev/projects/6">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-2">Monitoring, backups, security, handover documentation.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-2">+1: You make it production-grade — could someone else keep this running?</p>
    </Card>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div class="mt-10">
    <a
      href="/web-dev/getting-started"
      class="inline-block bg-primary hover:bg-primary-dark text-white font-semibold py-3 px-6 rounded-md transition-colors min-h-[44px]"
    >
      Get set up
    </a>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
